
'''= Swiss organization to promote eCulture, understood as codes of conducts within digital environment'''

URL = http://www.ynternet.org/

=Description=

"Ynternet.org aim is to promote eCulture, understood as codes of conducts within digital environment.

The preambule of its status includes a detailled description of this vision of STPDE develop and promote methodologies and platforms for cooperation projects through the Internet, providing equity of chances, promoting freedom of speech and quality standards in a knowledge economy and an information society.

Our formal mission statement is to define and promote eCulture, and it's links to Free Culture communities in digital environment : Free license, Free Software, Free documentations, Free Art, Free methodologies...

The name Ynternet.org asks the question « why Internet? ». We believe that « the Internet has emerged in our industrial society to answer to the need of a positive and long term globalisation process, within inter-connected social networks ».

Its activities include research and training for common good in the information society:

- Theorical research on STPDE and related issues, as well as applicative research for civil society

- ID,  trust & reputation processes for individuals and organisations, with augmented ePortfolios approaches

- eLearning, programmes for digital fluency and medias strategist

- International research and/or training programmes with various consortiums (example : www.wikiskills.net)   

- User's guides and sensibilisation campaigns within it's wiki publication «citoyens du net » ISSN 1664-4158
	
We believe that the social part of IT is the key issue for Ynternet.org. It means the key in this digitalised world are behaviours (the culture). This is why we concentrate on identifying, evaluating, empowering and spreading training modules, eLearning tools, virtual community contents management, conferences & workshops on eCulture, articles & publications...


Ynternet.org partners are as much governemental bodies (Swiss Secretariat for Education & research, Education Audivisual and Culture Executive Agency at EU) as international NGOs and United Nations (UN) System organization."
(https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ISjEjPnsZ97dwHaH-psBHvtmCGIut7-AlKb7IKv0YhY/edit)


In French:

'L'Association  Ynternet.org  a  été  créée  en  1998,  à  l'invitation  du
Département fédéral des affaires étrangères de la Confédération suisse, pour favoriser
la coopération internationale par Internet. Sa première réalisation a été l'installation d'un
réseau  de  coopération  internationale  intitulé  Cooperation.net,  visant  à  fournir
durablement des services Internet de base pour les francophones sensibles à la valeur
de la solidarité et pour faciliter leurs collaborations à distance sur des projets.                 
En 2006, Cooperation.net est l'un des principaux fournisseurs de services
Internet  solidaires  francophones,  avec  près  de  20'000  articles  et  plus  de  10'000
membres utilisateurs (organisations et personnes réparties sur plus de 35 pays).    
        
En  réussissant  à  installer  durablement  un  tel  réseau  de  coopération,
l'équipe  de  l'Association  Ynternet.org  a  développé  un  important  patrimoine
d'informations, de savoir-faire socio-technique et de partenaires dans le domaine
de la communication électronique, associant dynamique entrepreneuriale et sens
du bien commun. La direction de l'Association Ynternet.org a décidé de valoriser ce
patrimoine en passant ladite association en fondation sous l'égide de la Confédération
suisse."
(http://www.ynternet.org/ynternet.org/membres-d-ynternet.org/yorgstatuts-fondation-signes-new-2011-06-25-v2-def.pdf)

